Video processing stack (per CLAUDE.md):
- FFmpeg for transcoding, thumbnail generation, and segment extraction.
- OpenCV and PyAV for decode, frame sampling, and image operations.
- Frame extraction at configurable intervals for AI analysis; output to temp storage or S3.
- Live stream: ingest segments or frames for real-time/near-real-time pipeline.

Rules:
- Centralize video decode and frame extraction in dedicated utils or tools (e.g. app/utils/video_utils.py, app/ai/tools/frame_extractor.py).
- Do not block HTTP request path with heavy processing; use Celery tasks for upload processing and batch frame extraction.
- Validate input formats and codecs; enforce size and duration limits to avoid resource exhaustion.
- Store artifacts (thumbnails, sampled frames, segments) in S3 with consistent naming and TTL/retention where applicable.
- Use stable, reproducible sampling (e.g. by time interval or keyframe) so results are auditable.

Do not:
- Hardcode paths or bucket names; use config and env.
- Run unbounded FFmpeg/OpenCV jobs in the API process.
- Mix format-specific logic (e.g. RTMP vs HLS) in core analysis services; isolate in ingest/stream layer.
